defs.docs:
This is a Rust implementation of the [bip39][bip39-standard] standard for Bitcoin HD wallet
 mnemonic phrases.

defs.name: Mnemonic
defs.docs: The primary type in this crate, most tasks require creating or using one.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Generates a new [`Mnemonic`][Mnemonic]

defs.name: from_entropy
defs.docs: Create a [`Mnemonic`][Mnemonic] from pre-generated entropy

defs.name: from_phrase
defs.value: fn <S> (phrase: S, lang: Language) -> Result<Mnemonic, Error>
defs.docs: Create a [`Mnemonic`][Mnemonic] from an existing mnemonic phrase

defs.name: validate
defs.docs: Validate a mnemonic phrase

defs.name: phrase
defs.docs: Get the mnemonic phrase as a string reference.

defs.name: into_phrase
defs.docs: Consume the `Mnemonic` and return the phrase as a `String`.

defs.name: entropy
defs.docs: Get the original entropy value of the mnemonic phrase as a slice.

defs.name: language
defs.docs: Get the [`Language`][Language]

attributes.value: fail(display = "invalid number of words in phrase: {}", _0)

fail(display = "invalid entropy length {}bits for mnemonic type {:?}", _0,
       _1)

defs.name: MnemonicType
defs.docs: Determines the number of words that will be present in a [`Mnemonic`][Mnemonic] phrase

defs.name: for_word_count
defs.docs: Get a `MnemonicType` for a mnemonic phrase with a specific number of words

defs.name: for_key_size
defs.docs: Get a `MnemonicType` for a mnemonic phrase representing the given key size as bits

defs.name: for_phrase
defs.docs: Get a `MnemonicType` for an existing mnemonic phrase

defs.name: total_bits
defs.docs: Return the number of entropy+checksum bits

defs.name: entropy_bits
defs.docs: Return the number of entropy bits

defs.name: checksum_bits
defs.docs: Return the number of checksum bits

defs.name: word_count
defs.docs: Return the number of words

defs.name: Language
defs.value: Language::{English, ChineseSimplified, ChineseTraditional, French, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Spanish}
defs.docs:
The language determines which words will be used in a mnemonic phrase, but also indirectly
 determines the binary value of each word when a [`Mnemonic`][Mnemonic] is turned into a [`Seed`][Seed].

defs.name: wordlist
defs.docs: Get the word list for this language

defs.name: wordmap
defs.docs: Get a [`WordMap`][WordMap] that allows word -> index lookups in the word list

defs.name: Seed
defs.docs: The secret value used to derive HD wallet addresses from a [`Mnemonic`][Mnemonic] phrase.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Generates the seed from the [`Mnemonic`][Mnemonic] and the password.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: Get the seed value as a byte slice
